UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1542
1 AN ACT relating to a supplemental payment for recipients of a monthly retirement
2 allowance from the systems administered by the Kentucky Public Pensions Authority,
3 making an appropriation therefor, and declaring an emergency.
4 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
5 Section 1. Notwithstanding any provisions of KRS 42.205 and 61.691 to the
6 contrary and subject to the limitations established by this section, recipients of a monthly
7 retirement allowance from the Kentucky Employees Retirement System or State Police
8 Retirement System who have been retired for at least 12 months shall receive a one-time
9 supplemental payment added to their July 2026 retirement allowance payment, equal to
10 the monthly retirement allowance the recipient receives from the system in the month of
11 June 2026.
12 Section 2. There is hereby appropriated General Fund moneys in the amount of
13 $96,000,000 in fiscal year 2026-2027 from the Kentucky Permanent Pension Fund
14 established by KRS 42.205 to the Kentucky Public Pensions Authority to be applied to
15 the following funds to prefund the supplemental payment provided by Section 1 of this
16 Act:
17 (1) $84,000,000 to the Kentucky Employees Retirement Fund of the Kentucky
18 Employees Retirement System established by KRS 61.515 to prefund the supplemental
19 payment from the Kentucky Employees Retirement System to each recipient for service
20 in a nonhazardous position as defined in KRS 61.510(44);
21 (2) $7,000,000 to the Kentucky Employees Retirement Fund of the Kentucky
22 Employees Retirement System established by KRS 61.515 to prefund the supplemental
23 payment from the Kentucky Employees Retirement System to each recipient for service
24 in a hazardous position as provided in KRS 61.592; and
25 (3) $5,000,000 to the State Police Retirement Fund of the State Police Retirement
26 System established by KRS 16.510 to prefund the supplemental payment from the State
27 Police Retirement System to each recipient.
