UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1542
1 Section 3. The Board of Trustees of the County Employees Retirement System
2 may, by board decision, elect to provide recipients of a monthly retirement allowance
3 from the County Employees Retirement System who have been retired for at least 12
4 months a one-time supplemental payment added to their July 2026 retirement allowance
5 payment, equal to the monthly retirement allowance the recipient receives from the
6 system in the month of June 2026. If provided, the board shall fund the one-time
7 supplemental payment by increasing employer contribution rates to the County
8 Employees Retirement System, effective July 1, 2027, for a one-year or two-year period
9 as determined by the board to cover the full actuarial cost of the one-time payment.
10 Section 4. Whereas retired members and beneficiaries of the Kentucky
11 Employees Retirement System, County Employees Retirement System, and State Police
12 Retirement System have not received a cost-of-living adjustment to their retirement
13 allowances since fiscal year 2011-2012, an emergency is declared to exist, and this Act
14 takes effect upon its passage and approval by the Governor or upon its otherwise
15 becoming a law.
